Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addPGFTV(25.10)                                                addPGFTV(25.10)

Name
       addPGFTV - Inserts PGFTV cells at the prePlace and postRoute stages

Syntax
       addPGFTV

       [-help]

       [-area <x1> <y1> <x2> <y2>]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       [-prePlace]

       [-prefix <prefixName>]

       [-stepx <step_in_microns>]

       [-stepy <step_in_microns>]

       [-postRoute [-cell_list <{> <PGFTV1 PGFTV2 PGFTV3...}>]]

       Inserts PGFTV cells at the prePlace and postRoute stages.

Parameters
       -area <x1> <y1> <x2> <y2>
              Specifies  the  area in which PGFTV cells are to be inserted. If
              you do not specify any area, PGFTV cells will  be  inserted  for
              the complete core area.

              * x1: Specifies the area's lower left point on the x axis.

              * y1: Specifies the area's lower left point on the y axis.

              * x2: Specifies the area's upper right point on the x axis.

              * y2: Specifies the area's upper right point on the y axis.

       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of the single PGFTV cell to be inserted.

       -cell_list <{> <PGFTV1 PGFTV2 PGFTV3...}>
              Specifies  the  names  of  all PGFTV cells to be inserted at the
              postRoute  stage.  This  parameter  can  be  used  only  at  the
              postRoute  stage.  Otherwise,  tool will show the error message:
              "cell list is only for postRoute stage and could not be used  at
              other stage."

       -prePlace
              Specifies  the PGFTV insertion is for the pre-place stage. PGFTV
              cells are inserted by two constant values you set in  the  hori-
              zontal and vertical directions before placement. PGFTV insertion
              will  be  skipped  when there is blockage, macro, wellTap, power
              switches.

              PGFTV will be soft-fixed at this stage. It means  that  you  can
              move  PGFTV  to honor all placement rules. The tool supports the
              consecutive CPODE rule for PGFTV in refinePlace and addFiller.

       -prefix <prefixName>
              Specifies the prefix of the PGFTV cells to be inserted.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each addPGFTV parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man addPGFTV.

       -postRoute
              Specifies  the  PGFTV  insertion, before addFiller, at the post-
              route stage. Tool will insert PGFTV as much as possible  in  the
              whole design or in a specific region or a specific location. The
              tool  does  small  range prevention from violating all placement
              rules

              When the status of PGFTV will be "placed", they can be moved  or
              removed  for  DRC purpose and to honor maximum consecutive CPODE
              rule. The tool supports consecutive CPODE rule for PGFTV in  re-
              finePlace and addFiller.

       -prefix <prefixName>
              Specifies the prefix of the PGFTV cells to be inserted.

       -stepx <step_in_microns>
              Specifies the distance between PGFTV cells in the horizontal di-
              rection.  You  can use this parameter only at the preplace stage
              with -cell <cellName> and not with  -cell_list.

       -stepy <step_in_microns>
              Specifies the distance between PGFTV cells in the  vertical  di-
              rection.  You  can use this parameter only at the preplace stage
              with -cell <cellName> and not with -cell_list.

Examples
              *

                The following command adds PGFTV cells  of  type  PGFTV1  with
                spacing 20 at the prePlace stage:

                addPGFTV -preplace -cell PGFTV1 -stepx 20 -stepy 20

              *

                The  following  command inserts the PGFTV cells, PGFTV1 PGFTV2
                PGFTV3, at the postRoute stage.

                addPGFTV  -postRoute -cell_list {PGFTV1 PGFTV2 PGFTV3}

Related Information
              * addFiller

              * refinePlace

